universe of origin : the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored
seal               : Sega's handheld was, essentially, a Master System you could hold: the same Z80 CPU and a closely related video chip, behind a full-colour backlit screen. Vivid and capable next to the Game Boy — and so thirsty for batteries that its six AAs lasted only a few hours.
